http://www.thehindu.com/sport/cricket/Play-abandoned-on-day-four-of-3rd-test-at-SCG/article13984352.ece

Persistent rain washed out day four of the third test between Australia and West Indies at the Sydney Cricket Ground, almost certainly ensuring the match will end in a draw.Play was abandoned at 1300 local time (0200 GMT) as the West Indies remained on 248-7 in its first innings.No play has been possible since the evening session on day two due to inclement weather.Further rain is forecast for day five on Thursday.